@startuml
title QA Execution Gate

actor Human
participant PM
participant TL as "Tech Lead"
participant ENG as "Engineer"
participant REV as "Reviewer"
participant QA as "QA Engineer"
participant QAL as "QA Lead"
database KC as "Project QA Contract"

Human -> PM: Request feature / bug fix
PM -> TL: Structured issue + acceptance criteria
TL -> ENG: Assign implementation owner
TL -> REV: Assign reviewer
TL -> QA: Assign QA gate owner (optional)

ENG -> ENG: Implement change
ENG -> REV: SUBMIT_FOR_REVIEW + diff/test artifacts
REV -> REV: Review code / design / tests

alt Reviewer rejects
  REV -> ENG: REQUEST_CHANGES
else Reviewer approves and QA gate exists
  REV -> QA: APPROVE_IMPLEMENTATION => qa_pending
  QA -> KC: Load sanity profile / tool / fixture contract
  QAL -> QA: Validation policy / required evidence
  QA -> QA: Execute project-defined sanity tools
  QA -> QA: Run fixture-based validation
  QA -> TL: REQUEST_CHANGES with evidence
  QA -> TL: or APPROVE_IMPLEMENTATION with evidence
end

TL -> TL: CLOSE_TASK only after approval

note right of QA
QA is not a second reviewer.
QA must execute the built program,
use project tools/fixtures,
and attach structured evidence.
end note

@enduml
